It was a day like any other, and I got ready to go to class.
I have wished for this day to come for quite some time now; the opportunity to study something that I really wanted.

Some months ago I finished bachelor's, a time where I was feeling really stressed and overwhelmed. If someone asked me, it was one of the worst times of my life, but that changed a couple weeks ago.

For a few years now I have wanted to study computer science, but at the time I was told that I needed to pass bachelor's, and I did, but, finally, this year is completely different. At last I have the reins of my life or well, almost.
I had surgery relatively recently (a month and a half now) caused by a peritonitis by[speed=0.08]…[/speed]
Well, I’m not getting into details. The thing is that I had surgery and now I have to live a little differently because of a bag that I have glued to my skin, an [b]ostomy[/b].

