As the days went by my nerves grew exponentially.
In no time my surgery would come so I could go back to normal. They would get rid of the ostomy.
And that was one of my most important surgeries, because it would mean that soon my body would go back to being, relatively, normal. Maybe it wouldn’t work as before, I will surely never go back to being the same either way, but now I won’t have to live with this bag that has caused me so many issues.

